The paper deals with the problem of video hyperlinking, which involves analyzing and linking video fragments based on their content. This falls under the broad category of multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses statistical properties such as hubness and local intrinsic dimensionality, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for analyzing video content, and natural language processing (cs.CL) for understanding user expectations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.CL, in that order.
